Author: iampieman
Text: I just think the therapist’s reaction wasn’t how I pictured it exactly in my head, and I’m worried they think I was asking for nutrition advice when I meant I wanted help with the anxious thought about food. Also they’re not specifically trained for EDs or anything so I just feel ridiculous for bringing it up. Also I was complaining about how I hadn’t lost weight for 3 weeks and was freakin out/annoyed by it, which I regret. I don’t think you should say that to a therapist.   I don’t have another appointment for 9 days so I’m just gonna be regretting it until I can go and explain more then!   But thank-you, I might watch a movie to distract myself.

Author: 445saltedpeanuts
Text: If you're thinking about it this much, and it's causing you this much stress, then it IS a problem and you SHOULD bring it up in therapy.  You'll be ok. Do something nice today.
